{{Orphan|date=February 2017}} '''Jazz at the Maltings''' was a weekly series on BBC2 which featured some of the world's top jazz artists in concert at the [[Snape Maltings]].
The series, produced by Terry Henebury and directed by Vernon Lawrence was first aired in autumn 1968. It was introduced by jazz musician [[Benny Green (saxophonist)|Benny Green]].
